<div class="w3-container w3-padding-32 w3-row-padding">
  <div class="w3-content" style="width: 100%">
    <h1>MUSICAL TIME: RHYTHM & TEMPO</h1>
    <hr />
    <p>
      Dancing and music are completely intertwined, so learning how music works at a basic level is very important.
    </p>
    <p>
      Music is a timeline equally divided into <span class="w3-tag w3-green">bars</span>. Each bar is then divided into <span class="w3-tag w3-red">4</span> <span class="w3-tag w3-green">beats</span>. Constraining your movements to this underlying beat structure makes your dancing look “coordinated.”
    </p>
    <p>
      House-y EDM has a beat that goes <span class="w3-tag w3-red">kick ("thud")</span> <span class="w3-amber w3-text-white w3-tag">hihat ("tssk")</span> <span class="w3-blue w3-tag">clap ("thrash")</span> <span class="w3-amber w3-text-white w3-tag">hihat ("tssk")</span> (this repeats twice to form a bar). Kicks/Claps hit on each <span class="w3-tag w3-green">downbeat</span> of a bar, while Hihats hit in b/w beats. This pattern is called <span class="w3-tag w3-green">4 on the Floor</span>.
    </p>

    <div class="w3-container">
      <div class="w3-card w3-border-red w3-center">
        <iframe width="100%" height="140" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" allow="autoplay" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/401839872%3Fsecret_token%3Ds-c4Tno&amp;color=%23ff5500&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_comments=true&amp;show_user=true&amp;show_reposts=false&amp;show_teaser=true"></iframe>
        <img src="../img/Ableton.png" style="width:100%"/>
        <!-- <div class="w3-container w3-black w3-text-white">
          <p>Fig 1: A bar of house usually looks like this</p>
        </div> -->
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>
      When learning to shuffle, count these aloud like so:
    </p>
    <div class="w3-panel">
      <div class="w3-center w3-panel">
        <span class="w3-tag w3-red w3-xlarge">1</span>
        <span class="w3-tag w3-amber w3-text-white w3-xlarge">&</span>
        <span class="w3-tag w3-blue w3-xlarge">2</span>
        <span class="w3-tag w3-amber w3-text-white w3-xlarge">&</span>
        <span class="w3-tag w3-red w3-xlarge">3</span>
        <span class="w3-tag w3-amber w3-text-white w3-xlarge">&</span>
        <span class="w3-tag w3-blue w3-xlarge">4</span>
        <span class="w3-tag w3-amber w3-text-white w3-xlarge">&</span>
      </div>
      <div class="w3-center w3-panel">
        <span class="w3-opacity w3-tag w3-red w3-large">kick</span>
        <span class="w3-opacity w3-tag w3-amber w3-text-white w3-large">hihat</span>
        <span class="w3-opacity w3-tag w3-blue w3-large">clap</span>
        <span class="w3-opacity w3-tag w3-amber w3-text-white w3-large">hihat</span>
        <span class="w3-opacity w3-tag w3-red w3-large">kick</span>
        <span class="w3-opacity w3-tag w3-amber w3-text-white w3-large">hihat</span>
        <span class="w3-opacity w3-tag w3-blue w3-large">clap</span>
        <span class="w3-opacity w3-tag w3-amber w3-text-white w3-large">hihat</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>
      Again, there are 4 <span class="w3-tag w3-green">Beats</span> (the kick) in a <span class="w3-tag w3-green">bar</span>. There are <span class="w3-tag w3-blue">claps</span> layering over the <span class="w3-tag w3-red">kick</span> at downbeats 2 and 4. If you lose count, you can restart it on any beat. Here are some  barebones loops of 4 on the Floor you can practice with, one slow and one fast.
    </p>
    <iframe width="100%" height="285" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" allow="autoplay" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/playlists/453479820%3Fsecret_token%3Ds-9Sceb&amp;color=%23ff5500&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_comments=true&amp;show_user=true&amp;show_reposts=false&amp;show_teaser=true"></iframe>
