    <h1>TECHNIQUE TIP & GENRES</h1>
    <hr />
    <h2>The "Right" Technique</h2>
    <p>
      You’ll see people most commonly shuffle to music around 120 bpm (BEATS per minute). <br />
      HOWEVER: you can learn to shuffle to any EDM that is <span class="w3-tag w3-green">4 on the Floor</span>
      So...
    </p>

    <blockquote class="w3-panel w3-leftbar w3-border-amber">
      <p class="w3-large">
        <strong>Start practicing at 100bpm</strong> (e.g., electro house, nu disco, future chill, etc.). Move up gradually and your muscle memory will strengthen --- "Slow is smooth smooth is fast"
      </p>
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      Perfect each move and technique and gradually increase the speed at which you do it. Slowly but surely your muscle memory will strengthen. You'll save yourself loads of time in the macro by practicing the <strong class="w3-text-green">RIGHT technique</strong> (at slower speeds first). Do not accidentally practice the <strong class="w3-text-red">WRONG technique</strong>, or else you'll build the wrong muscle memory!
    </p>
